## Server: Albert (100.95.7.96)

Project root is at `/workspace/` (CLI mode) or `/workspace/{{ name }}/` (Web UI mode).
Check with: `ls /workspace/` — if you see `manage.py` you're at the root; if you see `{{ name }}/` go one level deeper.

⛔ **No local server.** Never run `manage.py runserver` or any dev server.
⛔ **No synthetic test data.** Test with real user-provided files. Use `deploy.py logs dev` for tracebacks.
⛔ **`localhost:5xxxx` ports in context are OpenHands internals** — not your app. Your app is at the deployed URL shown after `python3 .ymir/deploy.py dev`.

Deploy and verify:
```bash
cd /workspace && nohup python3 .ymir/deploy.py dev > /tmp/deploy.log 2>&1 & disown
sleep 30 && cat /tmp/deploy.log   # repeat until ✓ health check passed or ✗
python3 .ymir/deploy.py verify
# Errors? → python3 .ymir/deploy.py logs dev
```

